                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/65</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-08T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 30, 6 p.m. Investigate and report fully to Department as to legality
                    of decree calling for constitutional election of deputies by popular vote and
                    legality of calling for constitutional convention to assemble in May to form new
                    Constitution to elect a President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
